PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/01/01
TI  - Thermoclimate, Culture, and Poverty as Country-level Roots of Workers' Wages
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 40
EP  - 52
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
AB  - Most employees are under- or overpaid relative to their country's level of wealth. This 58-nation study makes a case for more temperate – less cold or hot – climate as a root of a more mastery-oriented culture, which in turn is associated with wealth-referenced overpayment. Overpayment is larger in poorer countries that also have a more temperate climate, a more mastery-oriented culture, or both. Supplementary examination of 25 rival predictors corroborated the conclusions.
